text: Gegeneophis seshachari, the Seshachari's caecilian, is a species of caecilian found in the Western Ghats of India. It is only known from its type locality Dorle village, Ratnagiri district in Maharashtra. ==References== seshachari Category:Endemic fauna of the Western Ghats Category:Amphibians of India Category:Amphibians described in 2003
